sections.content:
The occurrence of any of the following events shall constitute a default under this Agreement:

(a) Failure to make any payment when due;
(b) Breach of any representation, warranty, or covenant in this Agreement;
(c) Bankruptcy, insolvency, or assignment for the benefit of creditors by the Borrower;
(d) Any material adverse change in the Borrower's financial condition.

Upon the occurrence of a default, the Lender may declare the entire outstanding principal balance and all accrued interest immediately due and payable.
